THE first Chief Executive Officer of the Premier Soccer League (PSL) Trevor Phillips has passed away. The PSL announced the sad news of the passing of the British Bulldog, as Phillips was fondly known, in a statement today. "It is with great sadness that we announce the passing of Mr. Trevor “British Bulldog” Phillips, the first Chief Executive Officer of the Premier Soccer League," read the statemen. "The NSL Executive Committee conveys its heartfelt condolences to Mr. Phillips’ family, more particularly, his wife Stella and his children Mark and Sharon. We supplicate that GOD gives them fortitude at this moment of their extreme grief and pain. "The PSL will observe a moment of silence ahead of this week’s DStv Premiership and GladAfrica Championship fixtures. "May his soul repose peacefully."  It is with great sadness that we announce the passing of Mr. Trevor “British Bulldog” Phillips, the first Chief Executive Officer of the Premier Soccer League. pic.twitter.com/L6dXceSuE7 The NSL Executive Committee conveys its heartfelt condolences to Mr. Phillips’ family, more particularly, his wife Stella and his children Mark and Sharon. We supplicate that GOD gives them fortitude at this moment of their extreme grief and pain.  The PSL will observe a moment of silence ahead of this week’s DStv Premiership and GladAfrica Championship fixtures. May his soul repose peacefully. 